  <title>
    <phrase>Colorify</phrase>
  </title>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Colors</primary>
    <secondary>Colorify</secondary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Colorify</primary>
  </indexterm>
  <sect3>
    <title>
      <phrase>Overview</phrase>
    </title>
    <figure>
      <title>
        <phrase>
          Example for the <quote>Colorify</quote> filter
        </phrase>
      </title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/filters/examples/taj_orig.jpg" format="JPG"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption>
          <para>Original image</para>
        </caption>
      </mediaobject>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/filters/examples/color-taj-colorify.jpg" format="JPG"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption>
          <para>Filter <quote>Colorify</quote> applied</para>
        </caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <para>
      It renders a greyscaled image like it is seen through a colored glass.
      This filter works only on images in RGB mode.
    </para>
  </sect3>
  <sect3>
    <title>
      <phrase>Activate the filter</phrase>
    </title>
    <para>
      This filter is found in the image window menu under
      <menuchoice>
        <guimenu>Colors</guimenu>
        <guimenuitem>Colorify</guimenuitem>
      </menuchoice>.
    </para>
  </sect3>
  <sect3>
    <title>
      <phrase>Options</phrase>
    </title>
    <figure>
      <title>
        <phrase><quote>Colorify</quote> filter options</phrase>
      </title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/menus/colors-colorify.png" format="PNG"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Color</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            A color palette is available and you can select your own color
            by clicking on the <guilabel>Custom Color</guilabel> swatch.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </sect3>
</sect2>
